abstract: Haitian presidential candidate Jude Celestin, who finished second-place in first round of elections he deemed dubious, is not sure he will participate in runoff against government-backed candidate Jovenel Moise.
lead_paragraph: Jude Célestin said that “no decision has been made” about whether he will take part in the scheduled Dec. 27 runoff against Jovenel Moïse.

headline.main: Haiti: Presidential Candidate Says He May Not Compete in Runoff
headline.print_headline: The Americas; Haiti: Presidential Candidate Says He May Not Compete in Runoff
